111    /**
112    * <p>
113    * This class was introduced to avoid confusing handling of operator maps and other stuff when a new
114    * process definition is created. It is also necessary for file name resolving and breakpoint
115    * handling.
116    * </p>
117    *
118    * <p>
119    * If you want to use RapidMiner from your own application the best way is often to create a process
120    * definition from scratch (by adding the complete operator tree to the process' root operator) or
121    * from a file (for example created with the GUI beforehand) and start it by invoking the
122    * {@link #run()} method.
123    * </p>
124    *
125    * <p>
126    * Observers can listen to changes of the associated file, repository location, and context.
127    * </p>

- Uncovered Elements: 0 (0) Complexity: 1 Complexity Density: -
390    private void fireProcessStateChanged(int stateBefore, int newState) {...
391    // sanity check
392    if (stateBefore == newState) {
393    return;
394    }
395    List<ProcessStateListener> listeners;
396    synchronized (processStateListeners) {
397    listeners = new LinkedList<>(processStateListeners);
398    }
399    for (ProcessStateListener listener : listeners) {
400    switch (newState) {
401    case PROCESS_STATE_PAUSED:
402    listener.paused(this);
403    break;
404    case PROCESS_STATE_STOPPED:
405    listener.stopped(this);
406    break;
407    default:
408    if (stateBefore == PROCESS_STATE_STOPPED) {
409    listener.started(this);
410    } else {
411    listener.resumed(this);
412    }
413    break;
414    }
415    }
416   
417    }
